               <msContents>
                  <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Bodl_902-item1">
                     <author key="person_120695167">John Gower</author>
                     <title key="work_2706">Confessio Amantis</title>
                     <note>A good text of the first recension. The usual Latin rubrics and short verses occur. The first leaf of the manuscript is lost 
                        and the missing part of the prologue (as far as 'vppon a were') is supplied by a 16th century transcription; the 
                        transcription was most likely based on the 1554 edition of the third rescension of the 
                        <title>Confessio Amantis</title></note>
                        
                     <note>At the end of the manuscript is the metrical explicit (four lines only), 'Epistola super huius 
                     operis sui complementum...', beginning 'Quam cinxere freta'</note>
                     
                     
                     <note>The manuscript contains the early form of Gower's account of his three works</note>
                        
                     <textLang mainLang="enm" otherLangs="la">Middle English and Latin</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
